30/04/2004
STRASBOURG, France -- UNMIK chief Harri Holkeri told the European Parliament on Thursday (29 April) that those responsible for the anti-Serb riots in Kosovo last month would be brought to justice. He added that the instigators were extremists who do not represent the general public.
In Pristina, meanwhile, a UN spokesman said a Jordanian police officer has been remanded in custody for 30 days on suspicion he helped a fellow Jordanian policeman kill three Americans and injure 11 others. Three other Jordanians remain in detention. (VOA, AFP - 29/04/04)
